As \( n \to \infty \), the cascade of \( n \) independent binary symmetric channels (BSCs) with error probability \( p \) leads to an effective channel with vanishing capacity due to the exponential decay of mutual information. The capacity of a single BSC is \( 1 - H(p) \), where \( H(p) \) is the binary entropy, but cascading \( n \) such channels reduces the capacity to \( (1 - H(p))^n \), which tends to 0 as \( n \to \infty \).

